FT  07 AUG 92 / World Trade News: Coca-Cola set to open more plants in
Romania
ROMANIA is set to have two more Coca-Cola bottling plants, following
announcement of a Dollars 25m (Pounds 13m) investment from Leventis Group, a
Greek-Cypriot company, yesterday, Virginia Marsh reports from Bucharest.
Leventis, which runs six bottling plants in Bulgaria, plans to open
factories in two Romanian cities, Iasi and Oradea, next year. It will serve
the Transylvanian and Moldavian regions, a market of around 10m, with
Coca-Cola retaining Wallachia, including Bucharest.
